ug":"asa_318","score":1},{"id":"rec83PZfB7PGjHMh0","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Ahaziah","slug":"ahaziah_121","score":1},{"id":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Jerusalem","slug":"jerusalem_636","score":4},{"id":"rec5g1fzEKYzCO1Re","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Libnah","slug":"libnah_728","score":1}],"links":[{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec410yOewjNfbeE3","label":"part of"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recsyU2HqpyE9PeTo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recyNusCmwtrDBSab","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec91wntVnuliHv7E","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recGM8omzST49QfAW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"reczy1Y7fPcD5BDQh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recg7o6VW80KwLJz7","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recnZKcSQKs6KeS2b","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recD8WDUZtmlX6anv","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec0pylMTvkkfmwSw","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recbHLkz06CSe3C4K","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recaraSBvlHIwaaOB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec83PZfB7PGjHMh0","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reccTpc9fcBYBehiT","target":"rec5g1fzEKYzCO1Re","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec7dOphwYP5R3qkk","ref":"2Chr.21.1","text":"Now Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the city of David. And Jehoram his son reigned in his stead.","year":-889},{"id":"rec5iyqrRr3Rj1bXO","ref":"2Chr.21.2","text":"And he had brethren the sons of Jehoshaphat, Azariah, and Jehiel, and Zechariah, and Azariah, and Michael, and Shephatiah: all these were the sons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel.","year":-889},{"id":"rec010RyAp2ESUc3d","ref":"2Chr.21.3","text":"And their father gave them great gifts of silver, and of gold, and of precious things, with fenced cities in Judah: but the kingdom gave he to Jehoram; because he was the firstborn.","year":-889},{"id":"recNtD8GKYXDlO2Mt","ref":"2Chr.21.4","text":"Now when Jehoram was risen up to the kingdom of his father, he strengthened himself, and slew all his brethren with the sword, and divers also of the princes of Israel.","year":-889},{"id":"recj354JPTgctO9es","ref":"2Chr.21.5","text":"Jehoram was thirty and two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem.","year":-892},{"id":"recRlv7TI9aNeDHO3","ref":"2Chr.21.6","text":"And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, like as did the house of Ahab: for he had the daughter of Ahab to wife: and he wrought that which was evil in the eyes of the LORD.","year":-892},{"id":"rec39dzqWHfKQrPkt","ref":"2Chr.21.7","text":"Howbeit the LORD would not destroy the house of David, because of the covenant that he had made with David, and as he promised to give a light to him and to his sons for ever.","year":-892},{"id":"recfFCk2BxoTKNOrr","ref":"2Chr.21.8","text":"In his days the Edomites revolted from under the dominion of Judah, and made themselves a king.","year":-889}]}
